\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Let X be a discrete random variable with probability mass function p depending
 on a parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta.$
\end_inset

 Then the function 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
L(\theta|x)=p_{\theta}(x)=P_{\theta}(X=x)
\]

\end_inset

considered as a function of 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 is the likelihood function of 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 given the outcome x of the random variable X.
 
